==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shallop
<hw>Shal"lop</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>chaloupe</ets>, probably from D. <ets>sloep</ets>. Cf.
<er>Sloop</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[She] thrust the <qex>shallop</qex> from the floating strand.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>shallop</xex> is applied to boats of all
sizes, from a light canoe up to a large boat with masts and
sails.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shallot</ent>⟦br⟧
